nodes.bodyText:
I didn't test this, but my gut feeling is, that a normal loop along with the utility method is also very readable:
String commonLeadingWS(List<String> lines) {
  if (lines.size() < 2) return "";
  // start at second line since the first is left-trimmed in any case
  String current = Strings.repeat(" ", tabsToSpaces(lines.get(1)).length())
  for(int i = 1; i < lines.length; i++) {
    String next = lines.get(i);
    if (!isBlank(next))) {
      current = Strings.commonPrefix(current, tabsToSpaces(next));
    }
  }
  return current;
}

